overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria were met and to
  implement any identified missing features. The agent systematically addressed
  the user's request by first performing a detailed review and then proceeding
  with the implementation of several key features. This included adding a 1-10
  severity scale for tiredness with critical safety messaging, implementing
  detection logic for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and integrating placeholder outbound links to
  relevant sleep and mental health resources within the generated reports.
  Furthermore, the agent enhanced the Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring
  with weighted calculations, expanded the CSV export functionality to include
  all questionnaire responses, and introduced new questions for pain severity
  and chronic fatigue screening. The implementation involved updating data
  types, validation schemas, UI components, and report generation logic for both
  the web interface and PDF exports, ensuring a more robust and comprehensive
  questionnaire system.
